556,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-11 20:54:55+00:00,6865808,danilop/yas3fs,1565435,Liath,,,98486381,253043015,"In case anyone else came to this issue looking for a solution, I use something like this:
https://www.whaletech.co/2016/04/07/encryption-ephemeral-volumes-with-kms.html

With the yas3fs cache and mount point inside the encrypted partition. This way if the device is stolen I can revoke the key remotely making it (hopefully) impossible to decrypt the partition and gain access to the cache files or AWS credentials I use for mounting.

I'd just use normal LUKS authentication to mount the partition but the aforementioned device needs to live in a remote co-workers office and boot/mount this bucket without their interaction.",{},,User,False
