        bulkCmd,
        snmp_engine,
        CommunityData(community),
        transport((host, port)),
        ContextData(),
        # Non-repeating OIDs (use get-next for this number of entities).
        0,
        # Repeating OIDs (get as many of these as possible in bulk).
        16
    )
```

That is, I had been playing around with different values for the **Repeating OIDs** parameter. I tried a few different values, such as using the default of `50`, `64`, and `16`. I must have been trying with `16` when I hit this, because as soon as I changed it back to `16`, the traceback started occurring again.

I was following the pattern in the example code of grabbing the last element of the response array for that PDU and using it for the next `get-bulk` request. It just so happens that when I pass in the last element that comes back when I specify `16`, this exception occurs.",{},,User,False
