622,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-22 22:02:23+00:00,31262911,jaraco/keyring,109453,reece,,,161077200,227890717,"Here're results from lots of experimentation:

When dbus-python is installed by pip, either directly or indirectly via secretstorage requirements, you get a valid installation.

When dbus-python is installed by setuptools (sp. `python setup.py install` or `python setup.py develop`), an incomplete and non-functional dbus package is installed.

As a further test, I also built a tarball distribution for keyring with environment marker support included. It installed fine with pip even though the exact same code didn't work with setup.py.

So, here's what I think this means for this feature: we can include environment support and it will work without hassle (via pip) for users. However, developers will need to remember that they must manually install dbus-python (perhaps in a requirements-dev.txt file, or somesuch).

@jaraco: you cool with that?

---

Example (ubuntu 16.04, python 3.5.1):

```
(ve) snafu$ cd keyring

(ve) snafu$ reset-ve () { deactivate; rm -fr ve; pyvenv ve; source ve/bin/activate; pip install -U pip setuptools; }

(ve) snafu$ reset-ve 
...

# 1) install dbus-python and check what's really installed

(ve) snafu$ pip install dbus-python
...
Successfully installed dbus-python-1.2.4

(ve) snafu$ /bin/ls -l $VIRTUAL_ENV/lib/python3.5/site-packages/*dbus*
-rwxr-xr-x 1 reece reece   1014 Jun 22 14:28 /home/reece/projects/keyring/ve/lib/python3.5/site-packages/_dbus_bindings.la
-rwxr-xr-x 1 reece reece 571136 Jun 22 14:28 /home/reece/projects/keyring/ve/lib/python3.5/site-packages/_dbus_bindings.so
-rwxr-xr-x 1 reece reece   1083 Jun 22 14:28 /home/reece/projects/keyring/ve/lib/python3.5/site-packages/_dbus_glib_bindings.la
-rwxr-xr-x 1 reece reece  31104 Jun 22 14:28 /home/reece/projects/keyring/ve/lib/python3.5/site-packages/_dbus_glib_bindings.so

/home/reece/projects/keyring/ve/lib/python3.5/site-packages/dbus:
total 192
-rw-r--r-- 1 reece reece 17927 Jun 22 14:28 bus.py
-rw-r--r-- 1 reece reece   211 Jun 22 14:28 _compat.py
