1142,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-19 13:33:38+00:00,9289343,svinota/pyroute2,814602,svinota,,,218513175,295271843,"There are three built-in string types in the library so far:
1) `asciiz` — encode → `str + '\0'`; decode → up to `'\0'`
2) `cdata` — take the string as is
3) `string` — UTF-8 encoded

There is no strict length limitation, so if you encode `""bala""`, NLA becomes
```
length = 12  # header + data + zero terminator + alignment
data = ""bala\0""
```
or
```
length = 8 # header + data
data = ""bala""
```

So if you wanna define NLA:
```python
from pyroute.netlink import nla

class mydev(nla):
    nla_map = (('IFLA_MYDEV_UNSPEC', 'none'),  # NLA type 0
               ('IFLA_MYDEV_DEV', 'asciiz'),  …)  # NLA type 1, …
```

And vice verse, upon decoding the library takes into account the real header value, and decodes up to `""\0""` (`asciiz`) or whole (`cdata`, `string`)",{},,User,False
