2296,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-11 04:40:28+00:00,5378330,ui/django-post_office,431110,cberzan,,,283562214,380324954,"I'm seeing the same problem with post_office 3.0.4, Django 1.11.10, without using Celery at all. Sending emails from the shell starts failing after a while, with ""Server not connected"" and ""please run connect() first"" in the post_office logs. In the postfix logs, I see ""timeout after END-OF-MESSAGE"" as mentioned in a previous comment.

Looking through the code, I suspect the connection cache (connections.py) is to blame. Suppose we start with an empty cache, and we send an email with `mail.send(..., priority='now')`. That would cause a connection to be opened [here](https://github.com/ui/django-post_office/blob/62aa4aa516e9ae87d700fb4dee43c473aceb7434/post_office/connections.py#L32), but then it seems like we never close that connection. After 5 minutes, postfix says ""timeout after END-OF-MESSAGE"" and closes our connection. If we try to send an email after that, we will reuse the stale connection from the cache, which results in a ""Server not connected"" / ""please run connect() first"" error.

@yprez and other contributors, can you confirm that this is the issue? And if so, what's the best way to fix it?",{},NONE,User,False
