2467,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-14 14:32:51+00:00,30379674,adamchainz/django-mysql,857609,adamchainz,,,303183524,381333236,"Sorry this affected you too @natecox. The fix was in the end fairyl simple, in fact all the other field classes already had correct `deconstruct()` methods, but it was missed in JSONField. There was actually an analogous bug in Django django/django#3765 - I started the fields in Django-MySQL based on the fields in `django.contrib.postgres`, hence this path-simplifying logic was copied over before the fix had been applied to master, I guess I missed applying it to JSONField. Release 2.2.1 is out now with the fix.

> I just hit this issue today and lost a day debugging it. Until a proper fix makes its way upstream, can we add a big warning to the docs about subclassing?

I understand you must have been frustrated you spent so much time tracking down your bug. However, I didn't find this comment particularly motivating, as I read it as a bit 'entitled'. I develop this software entirely in my spare time as a labour of love. I'm sure you appreciate this :)",{},OWNER,User,False
