2544,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-02 07:43:45+00:00,70798890,logandk/serverless-wsgi,20273,logandk,,,233086164,305714639,"Thanks for the work and PR! 👍

As you've found the response body always to be `bytes` on Python 3.6, this patch will base64 encode all response bodies. This should only really make sense for actual binary responses, rather than e.g. `text/html`, considering the overhead of encoding.

> If body is a binary blob, you can encode it as a Base64-encoded string and set isBase64Encoded to true. http://docs.aws.amazon.com/apigateway/latest/developerguide/api-gateway-set-up-simple-proxy.html

So, in the case of non-binary responses, I reckon `response.data.decode('utf-8')` would be sufficient. Perhaps the logic could be altered to:

* If the payload is binary (whitelisting by mime-type, as Zappa does, is probably the simplest way to go, as opposed to something like libmagic)
  * Base64 encode the response (this should work the same way on both Python 2.7 and 3.6, I think)
* Else
  * If Python version is 3.6 and type is `bytes`, decode to a `str`

Finally, on Python 2.7, where `bytes` and `str` are the same thing, the utf-8 decoding operation should not happen.

What do you think?",{},,User,False
2545,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-29 18:24:31+00:00,9376661,lorenzofox3/Smart-Table,3590915,mathewguest,,,136903502,298185911,"Here's another ugly hack based on dg14's that puts the logic in the st-persist directive. I needed to do this because I wasn't using st-pipe/callServer(tableState) so I didn't know a good way to access tableState from the parent controller.

	//save the table state every time it changes
	scope.$watch(function () {
	    return ctrl.tableState();
	}, function (newValue, oldValue) {

	
	    if (newValue.pagination.start2) {
		    // consume start2
		    if (newValue.pagination.start2 < newValue.pagination.totalItemCount) {
			newValue.pagination.start = newValue.pagination.start2;
			newValue.pagination.start2 = undefined;
		    }
	    }

	    if (newValue !== oldValue) {
		localStorage.setItem(nameSpace, JSON.stringify(newValue));
	    }
	}, true);

	//fetch the table state when the directive is loaded
	if (localStorage.getItem(nameSpace)) {
	    var savedState = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(nameSpace));
	    var tableState = ctrl.tableState();

	    angular.extend(tableState, savedState);
	    tableState.pagination.start2 = tableState.pagination.start;
	    ctrl.pipe();
	}",{},,User,False
