3216,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-17 21:13:55+00:00,26947860,facelessuser/pymdown-extensions,1055125,facelessuser,,,258317889,330089018,"Okay.  I took a look:

1.  I don't think you can use the `startinline` is a valid option.  Only certain languages have additional options, and they will be listed under the associated lexer at http://pygments.org/docs/lexers/.  Check out PHP and you'll see what I mean.

2. When I did the following, it worked as expected:
 
    ```
      - pymdownx.highlight:
          css_class: codehilite
          extend_pygments_lang:
            - name: php-inline
              lang: php
              options:
                startinline: true
            - name: shell
              lang: console
    ```

    I imagine you are expecting the dollar sign to be highlighted, but depending on the color scheme used, this might not be the case.  With the color scheme provided by Material, the dollar sign does not get highlighted, but it is properly scoped with `gp`. The first code block was done with shell mapped to console, the second is console directly:

    ![screenshot 2017-09-17 15 10 51](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1055125/30524948-80a8fc40-9bba-11e7-9821-55ec863d515c.png)
",{},OWNER,User,False
