It's a bug in plone.rest (https://github.com/plone/plone.rest/issues/50). My project depends on collective.solr which uses plone.restapi. plone.restapi registers services for `POST` using the `plone:service`-directive. As soon as any such service is registered the upload will fail: 

```
  <plone:service
      method=""POST""
      name=""@foo""
      for=""Products.CMFCore.interfaces.ISiteRoot""
      factory="".foo.Bar""
      permission=""cmf.ManagePortal""
      />
```

The traverser of plone.rest handles the POST-request and the ``fileUpload`` of `plone.app.content` method is never used. For more detail in th original issue.
I can fix it in my project by using a source-checkout of the branch with includes the fix. Thanks @buchi for fixing it. 
The fix will be included in plone.rest 1.0b1",{},,User,False
