3758,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-06 05:49:21+00:00,8463294,mozilla/treeherder,3660661,tojonmz,131524,mozilla,102230759,138043554,"Not to hijack the PR, but here's my proposal for the new *'runnable'*, and pending, and running jobs.

Adding a few folks for visibility, @rvandermeulen @KWierso @camd @edmorley @jonallengriffin 

Rationale:
* we use an adjacent symbol (star*) for classified jobs - why not use this concept for other states?
* leverage that concept for the new 'runnable', and also pending jobs
* these states are always transient so exert no permanent UI distraction
* this is partly inspired by Travis CI state colors (amber, green) during a run

I did about 10-12, these ended up being my favorites so far. The green triangle is actually bootstrap 'yellowgreen'. Both it and the open square hold up well at normal size in Treeherder on my monitor. Runnable and pending are so similar in concept, I pose they should share the same grey and be differentiated by the symbol (and its color for those not colorblind).

Mockups in each row below:
* running is the first job, and is unchanged
* pending is the second job in lightgrey
* runnable is the third job also in lightgrey

My favorite:
![fa-square-o_runnable](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3660661/9702642/5504beda-5436-11e5-90cc-8f4b8cad3315.jpg)
Another alternate but fa-spinner didn't hold up as well:
![fa-spinner-pending](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3660661/9702644/5e9988a4-5436-11e5-849f-305221cdb572.jpg)
Other variation with fa-poweroff for runnable, but didn't hold up as well:
![fa-poweroff_runnable](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3660661/9702646/697662a6-5436-11e5-81c7-9068b5370ff9.jpg)
Other variation but circle wasn't as strong as square - which is more evocative of 'stopped'
![fa-circle-o_runnable](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/3660661/9702647/6cb69486-5436-11e5-8a83-d86b9c04a7b0.jpg)

This treatment should also work fine with (+n) job counts. If we're interested in pursing this, let me know and I will split this off into a separate bug/PR that we can land at the same time as this one :)",{},,User,False
