3997,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-28 05:53:55+00:00,24774658,boto/boto3,821550,rayluo,327752,boto,101114520,143646048,"@adepue In general, you are always welcome to help. For this specific case, we tend to and are still trying to address it in a way that every AWS SDK (7 in total) can automatically pick up the new fix. Before that happens, you can have a workaround in your python code like this:

    def post_it(request, operation_name, **kwargs):
        if request.method == 'GET':  # You can also add one more condition size > THRESHOLD
            request.headers['Content-Type'] = 'application/x-www-form-urlencoded'
            request.method = 'POST'
            request.url, request.data = request.url.split('?')

    client = boto3.client('cloudsearchdomain', endpoint_url='http://search-your-domain.com')
    client.meta.events.register('request-created.cloudsearchdomain.Search', post_it)  # The magic
    client.search(query='a long long long long ... (8192 bytes) ... query string')  # It works!
",{},,User,False
3998,IssueCommentEvent,2015-10-30 13:56:03+00:00,24774658,boto/boto3,3948729,tsunghao,327752,boto,111942733,152532132,">1) Clarification needed: Should each file be added individually, is adding folders ok, or does it not matter?

