>2)  It should be noted to run ""pyinstaller [options] {your_prog}.spec"" to compile

Yes. Because pyinstaller doesn't provide argument to expend **datas** with CLI tool

>3) s3_session._loader.search_paths.append(""{step1_path}"")

simple example in my case:
**s3.spec**
datas=[('C:\\Python27\\Lib\\site-packages\\botocore\\data\\_endpoints.json', 'data'),
            ('C:\\Python27\\Lib\\site-packages\\botocore\\vendored\\requests\\cacert.pem', 'data')... ],
(not all of them)

The first one is **what you want** and the second one is **where you want it be**.

**s3.py**
s3_session = Session(aws_access_key_id='{key_id}',
                                   aws_secret_access_key='{secret_key}',
                                   region_name='us-east-1')
s3_session._loader.search_paths.append('data')

",{},,User,False
