4030,IssueCommentEvent,2016-09-19 21:02:24+00:00,49535299,boto/s3transfer,4605355,kyleknap,327752,boto,176961314,248125576,"@jamesls Alright so I updated the PR to rely on the state transitioning of the ``TransferCoordinator`` to know when to announce done, instead of having the logic in the ``SubmissionTask``. The logic now is if ``TransferCoordinator`` is in a ``not-started`` state and the transfer gets cancelled then announce done to ensure that done actually get announced. I also started adding some state transitioning logic to help validate some of these transitions and make sure states do not get clobbered.

As to fixing the semantics of ``done()`` (i.e. done meaning at a final state and the event has been announced), this I think can be addressed in a separate PR because it is a decently sized change.",{},,User,False
