4553,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-17 18:59:21+00:00,9252533,numenta/nupic,15566,rhyolight,1039191,numenta,106461706,141189212,"I think I know what is going on here. This is happening to several people in different ways, but it always boils down to a the same `NUPIC_CORE_RELEASE` exception. 

Our last releases, 0.2.6 & 0.2.7, produced bad binary files for `nupic.bindings` on pypi. I believe that fixed this problem in the source code, but we never bumped the `nupic.bindings` version for a re-release on pypi. So people have a bad version of bindings in their pip cache, and very potentially on pypi itself. 

@oxtopus Just released a new version of [`nupic.bindings`](https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/pull/614), which is building in CI now and should deploy to https://pypi.python.org/pypi/nupic.bindings as version 0.2 soon. Once this happens, we'll also need to version bump NuPIC to pick up that version change.

Please standby and we'll let you know when the releases are complete so you can try again. In the meantime if you want to try to install, you'll have to do it from the latest source code and figure out how to remove any lingering versions of `nupic.bindings` you might have in a local pip cache. ",{},,User,False
