5082,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-12 07:38:52+00:00,3470471,FortAwesome/Font-Awesome,556268,tagliala,1505683,FortAwesome,304250140,372217566,"Hi!

Thanks for being part of the Font Awesome Community.

> How come you kept fa-envelope and removed fa-email?

AFAIK, there has never been an alias `email` for `envelope`:
- https://github.com/FortAwesome/Font-Awesome/blob/fa-4/src/icons.yml#L2238
- https://github.com/FortAwesome/Font-Awesome/blob/fa-4/css/font-awesome.css
- https://jsfiddle.net/tagliala/0xt7wf4f/ (no icon)

There is definitely a documentation filter for email, in fact so you will see `envelope` when you search for `email`

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/556268/37270392-ef1fb76a-25ce-11e8-9de4-e227a9a22947.png)

I know that email could be a better name for this icon, but we cannot change it in FA5 because it will be a breaking change and alias have been dropped.

Ref: https://fontawesome.com/how-to-use/upgrading-from-4

Hope it helps, closing here

PS: The choice of `envelope` goes back to the days of Bootstrap 2, because at the time FA has been a replacement of Glyphicons. Ref: https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap/blob/v2.3.2/less/sprites.less#L55
",{},MEMBER,User,False
