5369,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-09 04:41:28+00:00,59868262,aws/chalice,206176,kadrach,2232217,aws,312292801,379629330,"Thanks for the link, didn't know about that.

To address your issue, you can make use of the `chalice package` workflow, which generates a SAM template that is deployed through CloudFormation:

```
# Contains the archive and template
chalice package out/  
# Outputs *CloudFormation template*
aws cloudformation package --template-file out/sam.json --s3-bucket mybucket
```
The `aws cloudformation package` command will upload the archive to S3, and output a SAM template containing

```
Resources:
  APIHandler:
    Properties:
      CodeUri: s3://mybucket/92a8af20a990fc350d0c5c7023c89cc6
```

Prior to deploying this template, you should be able to mess with the object in S3 or the template.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
