5686,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-03 03:25:07+00:00,7137821,cloudtools/troposphere,220180,rcuza,3028687,cloudtools,46333560,230133188,"@jeanphix - It was not consistent with other functions in the script in how it was laid out, but it looks like commit da7e7fc is consistent. 

I may of used the serious adjectives because I have a different preference when I align attributes for a function. In hind sight, my preference is not a good enough reason to seriously criticize the style. My apologies. To go into too much detail, 3aad426 commit aligned the closing parenthesis  with the 'd' in `def`and put the attributes at four spaces:

```
def create_stack(
    conn,
    stackname,
    template=None,
    url=None,
    params=None,
    capabilities=None,
):
```
I prefer to have the closing parenthesis be aligned with the attributes and the attributes aligned with the opening parenthesis:
```
def create_stack(conn,
                 stackname,
                 template=None,
                 url=None,
                 params=None,
                 capabilities=None,
                 ):
``` 

The most important thing is to be consistent throughout the script. 
",{},,User,False
