5707,IssueCommentEvent,2015-05-05 18:05:16+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,512764,benjyw,3065172,pantsbuild,67616099,99160853,"As for the size of the data - that blob is what JMake needs, apparently. 

Using the isolated strategy is akin to making the file ""random access"", in that each target's data is in a separate file. But you still have huge lines, not much we can do about that without modifying jmake. 

However we do have that change pending to compile Java with Zinc instead of JMake. And I've put a lot of effort into optimizing operations on Zinc's analysis files, which no one has yet done for JMake. 

So it might be worth waiting until that change lands and seeing how that improves your build times. And then we can decide if we want to hang on to JMake, and if so we can do some optimization work on its analysis operations. 

We just use almost no Java internally at Foursquare, so JMake was never a priority for us.",{},,User,False
