5765,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-26 23:25:06+00:00,93721432,awslabs/sockeye,455256,mjpost,3299148,awslabs,278270702,384818447,"I added an integration test and it completes fine, but I haven't added a system test yet.

I think the kinds of unit tests that would be best here would be to add a k-best output option to the decoder, and then to manually inspect the beam for differences that result from applying different beam thresholds. During this last rebase, I would often find bugs that didn't show up until I decoded entire test sets and noticed a drop in corpus-level BLEU, so the existing tests are too coarse to be useful. What do you think of this? One option would be to use the existing JSON object returned by `--output-type beam_store`, but it might be nicer to have a k-best interface (this is also something that I've seen requested in a number of different places, and also in private conversations).

As a second, related proposal, I would suggest merging this code in now, but also creating an issue registering the need for tests based on inspecting the beam (to make sure it happens), and then adding that test in a separate commit. The reason I want to commit now is because I am worried about the beam search code changing in the meantime and having to rebase again (or having someone else start a project on the beam, and them having to rebase). I can commit to writing the test by the end of next week.",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
