6246,IssueCommentEvent,2015-04-08 15:22:09+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,324506,Blystad,6117407,deis,53052185,90948733,"Alright! I have a Deis environment now running completely without deis-store.

I'll post my findings now so we can figure out the way ahead:

First of all, my environment is now running with:
* PostgreSQL running on Amazon RDS
* Amazon S3 bucket in the same region as Deis (eu-west-1) 
* [Logs redirected to papertrail.](http://docs.deis.io/en/latest/managing_deis/platform_logging/#application-log-drain)

First of all, some configuration needs to be done. See [this gist for the settings I've used](https://gist.github.com/Blystad/136eff426ba8cc2b2423)

Then there are a couple of problems which needs to be sorted out:

- [ ] **`deis-controller` requires `/var/lib/deis/store` folder for logs.**

If this folder is not created then docker will not allow `deis-controller` to start.

- [ ] **`deis-controller` requires `deis-store-volume` to start**
- [ ] **`deis-logger` requires `deis-store-volume` to start**
- [ ] **`deis-logger` requires `/var/lib/deis/store` folder to start**
- [ ] **`deis-registry` requires `BUCKET_NAME` set as environment variable #3429**
- [ ] **`deis-registry` can't start since it fails to create a bucket, because of a inproper check in the `create-bucket` script #3430**

I propose that we create a fake `deis-store-volume` unit file which has one job - ensure that `/var/lib/deis/store` is created on all hosts. This will please `deis-controller` and `deis-logger` and allow them to start. 

And also fix issue #3429 and #3430. I'm going to test this in production now.",{},,User,False
