6465,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-17 09:29:19+00:00,16557526,pysam-developers/pysam,14112172,vladie0,6598771,pysam-developers,206774568,280600807,"Dear AndreasHeger, 

Thank you for your fast response, 
I suspect I've found the error behind my output. When I generate the output in the following way:
    infile = pysam.AlignmentFile((directory+name+'.sam'), ""r"")
    outfile = pysam.AlignmentFile((directory+name+'.bam'), ""wb"", template=infile)
    for s in infile:
        outfile.write(s)

print pysam.sort(""-O"", ""SAM"", ""error.bam"")'
only the first line is printed in the final output. However when infile and outfile are closed prior to sorting, the correct output is generated. I suspect that there is a delay between writing and saving.

