6466,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-23 06:34:25+00:00,16557526,pysam-developers/pysam,1900459,kyleabeauchamp,6598771,pysam-developers,142855215,200208078,"So the issue here is that the samtools calls return bytes on py3k and strings on py2k.  This means that users (and tests) cannot do `line.split(""\"")` because the tab is a string, not a byte object.  Not sure what the right answer is longterm, but at least this fixes the tests. ",{},,User,False
