6480,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-18 16:33:26+00:00,26829379,VUnit/vunit,4018223,kraigher,6691399,VUnit,315312511,382449176,"Spontaneously it seems like a lot of complexity just to avoid installing VUnit in the container.

I infer that your problem is that you want to bumb the VUnit version often and it creates the need for many containers.  Wouldn't the easiest solution just be to just run VUnit from within the container but have the VUnit repo outside of the container. As long as VUnits only dependency (colorama) is installed in the container you can just set the PYTHONPATH to the VUnit repo and map the repo root to the container to run it without any ""install"". When I run VUnit i never install it with setup.py or pip I just set the PYTHONPATH in the shell.",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
