6532,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-20 22:10:07+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,5723682,tjprescott,6844498,Azure,258997024,330995240,"@JasonRShaver the idea is that you and/or @mayurid would give the onboarding team the contact info of one of the CLI devs and that dev would be the one to do the kickoff meeting, command reviews and PR review, and that choice will likely depend on other factors.  I can put the generic workgroup alias for general questions, and/or links to our public question channels. On that note... which ones would you want?

For time estimates, it really depends on the scope of their module and, hopefully I stressed this in the guide, the amount of early feedback and periodic review they get from us. Trying to charge ahead blindly takes a long time spent fumbling, and then a lot of time to review (because it will usually have a lot of issues) and then a lot of rework time. So I'm not sure I could say anything not incredibly vague on that. 
",{},MEMBER,User,False
6534,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-20 23:26:40+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,5723682,tjprescott,6844498,Azure,237330264,309919757,"Ideally the REST calls would only be made if the user explicitly ran the command with --verbose or --debug. That's why I deferred to your judgement on whether the logger approach is adequate.  If they are synonymous then that's perfect.

