6644,IssueCommentEvent,2017-06-22 18:53:42+00:00,39039065,Azure/azure-storage-python,8151045,gregdegruy,6844498,Azure,237699711,310470242,"Found the solution. I needed to include a sas token in my upload request.

This should be included in the docs in some way, how can I help include this in the docs?

```
# i use this little hack to get a properly formatted blob name first
blobName = block_blob_service.get_blob_to_path(IPutmycontainernameHere, IPutMyBlobPathAndNameHere, INameMyLocalFile).name

# then I make a sas token
sas_url = block_blob_service.generate_blob_shared_access_signature(IPutmycontainernameHere, blobName, BlobPermissions.READ, datetime.utcnow() + timedelta(hours=1))

# then I make a properly formatted blob URL
generated_blob_url = block_blob_service.make_blob_url(
    container_name= IPutmycontainernameHere,
    blob_name=blobName,
    sas_token=sas_url,
)
```

```
#-----------------------------------------
# Uploading Video to Video Indexer Service
#-----------------------------------------
headers = {
    'Content-Type': 'multipart/form-data',
    'Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key': I_put_my_VIDEO_INDEXER_API_KEY_here,
}
params = urllib.urlencode({
    'name': 'NameOfVideo',
    'privacy': 'Public',
    'videoUrl': generated_blob_url
})
try:
    conn = httplib.HTTPSConnection('videobreakdown.azure-api.net')
    conn.request(""POST"", ""/Breakdowns/Api/Partner/Breakdowns?%s"" % params, ""{body}"", headers)
    response = conn.getresponse()
    data = response.read()
    print('Complete')
    print('Video ID: ' data)
    conn.close()
except Exception as e:
    print(""[Errno {0}] {1}"".format(e.errno, e.strerror))
