6724,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-28 12:08:32+00:00,13258039,aio-libs/aiohttp,158029,pieterb,7049303,aio-libs,244637060,318635557,"It the same time, however, my colleague @evertlammerts was reviewing my code. He'd been using aiohttp before, and told me my code was hard to read and understand, partly because he thought I wasn't doing things the ""aiohttp-way"".

So I refactored my code, stopped implementing my own AbstractResource-classes, and started using `UrlDispatcher` more like the documentation suggests I should.

So everything's ok for now. By offering the `register_resource()` method, you still do support custom Resource classes (which must implement `AbstractResource`), is that right? If so, I'm still a bit confused why the functionality in `PlainResource` and `DynamicResource`, which is very common, shouldn't be part of aiohttp's public interface.",{},,User,False
