6797,IssueCommentEvent,2015-11-25 17:33:06+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,57394,fperez,7388996,jupyter,118230517,159682515,"On Wed, Nov 25, 2015 at 9:05 AM, Brian E. Granger <notifications@github.com>
wrote:

> 1) Fix the ordering of everything for 4.1, preserving the keyboard
> behaviors.
> 2) Change nothing for 4.1, but everything for 5.0.
> 3) Temporarily re-order the ""Restart Kernel"" to match everything else for
> 4.1, but then change the order of everything for 5.0.
>

Ah, got it. My only concern with 1 is that I think if that reordering is
done, they shouldn't be called `Cancel, OK`, they should become named
actions. So the audit will have to be more thorough and careful, and there
will be decisions to make on the name of *every* button. That means this
becomes a potentially very long and detailed PR in terms of how many things
to look at (not that much code, obviously).

That worries me a bit, given we're trying to wrap up and ship...


-- 
