7908,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-12 15:20:34+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,61316,milliams,13271048,ganga-devs,154240430,218790893,"I would have very much liked to see a set of tests being submitted along with such a large new feature as this. Due to @drmarkwslater's recent work on GangaLHCb, we can now run tests on plugins so some simple tests, even just to make sure that the modules can be imported are important.",{},,User,False
7911,IssueCommentEvent,2016-02-08 13:02:30+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,1102021,rob-c,13271048,ganga-devs,131693407,181356864,"This still happens when the tests are isolated enough that they run in a unique directory to one another.

The Monitoring service should not persist beyond a ```tearDown``` as I call the standard atexit functions which should kill all running threads and flush and close the registries.

With that in mind; there are problems with some Monitoring threads not exiting cleanly. (I suspect I understand why in another branch but have yet to backport the 'fix' to something closer to develop)
I'll have a stab at implementing this and see if it helps.

I've even got a tearDownClass method in my copy of GangaUnitTest which wipes the repo from disk every time Ganga exists which still doesn't solve this problem, so the problem doesn't appear to persist on disk.


I appreciate merging this branch is a pain if it causes issues from the unittests persective but if the unittests are broken by the _fixes_ in this branch then I'm beginning to think this should be a separate issue to address what is broken there. Otherwise I risk adding a lot of unittest changes to this code which weren't intended to be part of this branch.",{},,User,False
