7950,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-14 00:56:17+00:00,30212825,Amber-MD/pytraj,4451957,hainm,13525542,Amber-MD,213636697,286289715,"@drroe I narrow down the issue and seems like the the leak is from `GetFrame` in cpptraj. Any idea why?

```python
    def __iter__(self):
        '''iterately getting Frame instance
        '''
        cdef int i
        cdef int n_atoms = self.n_atoms
        cdef int n_frames = self.n_frames

        # use `frame` as buffer
        cdef Frame frame = Frame()

        # del frame.thisptr # do not do this.
        frame.thisptr[0] = self.thisptr.AllocateFrame()

        for i in range(n_frames):
            # do not create new Frame inside this loop to reduce memory
            self.thisptr.GetFrame(i, frame.thisptr[0])
            if self._being_transformed:
                self._do_transformation(frame)
            yield frame
```

If I comment the line
```self.thisptr.GetFrame(i, frame.thisptr[0])```, there won't be any extra memory.

turn off `GetFrame`
==============
```python
 Line #    Mem usage    Increment   Line Contents
================================================
    13     49.0 MiB      0.0 MiB   @profile
    14                             def process_traj(traj):
    15                                 # for chunk in traj.iterchunk(chunk_sz, start=0, stop=-1):            
    16     49.0 MiB      0.1 MiB       for frame in traj:
    17     49.0 MiB     -0.0 MiB           pass
```

turn ON (leak)
==========
```python
Line #    Mem usage    Increment   Line Contents
================================================
    13     48.9 MiB      0.0 MiB   @profile
    14                             def process_traj(traj):
    15                                 # for chunk in traj.iterchunk(chunk_sz, start=0, stop=-1):            
    16     73.2 MiB     24.3 MiB       for frame in traj:
    17     73.2 MiB     -0.0 MiB           pass
```

PS: Using `tz2.ortho.nc`",{},,User,False
