8041,IssueCommentEvent,2016-08-12 14:47:22+00:00,48733333,Neurosim-lab/netpyne,8440562,salvadord,14202113,Neurosim-lab,170191659,239466442,"As you know the way cells are connected in parallel Neuron is using pc.gid_connect(), which for the presyn cell only takes a cell gid. The way to associate a different presyn source of spikes is to specify it when you associated the gid with the cell using the pc.cell() command. 

netpyne allows to specify a different source of spikes for a cell by setting the 'spikeGenLoc' param in the corresponding section. See the Traub or Friesen models for examples: http://neurosimlab.org/netpyne/advanced.html#traub-model 
http://neurosimlab.org/netpyne/advanced.html#friesen-model

Please, let me know if that works for what you need to do, or you need something else. thx",{},,User,False
