8115,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-20 03:43:24+00:00,43056951,graphql-python/graphene,5723225,HelloYie,15002022,graphql-python,155683608,220510269,"* graphene==0.9.1
* Django==1.9.6

## My profile model:

```
from django.db import models
from django.contrib.auth.models import User

class Profile(models.Model):

    user = models.OneToOneField(
        User,
        verbose_name=u""user"",
        related_name=""profile"",
        null=False,
        blank=False,
    )
    nickname = models.CharField(
        max_length=20,
        verbose_name=u'nickname',
        null=True,
        blank=True,
    )

    class Meta:
        verbose_name = u'personal info'
        verbose_name_plural = u'personal info'

```

## My schema:

```
import graphene
from graphene import relay
from graphene.contrib.django import DjangoNode
from django.contrib.auth.models import User as UserModel
from graphene.contrib.django.filter import DjangoFilterConnectionField
from graphene.contrib.django.debug import DjangoDebugPlugin
from apps.profile.models import Profile as ProfileModel

class User(DjangoNode):
    class Meta:
        model = UserModel

class Profile(DjangoNode):
    class Meta:
        model = ProfileModel

schema = graphene.Schema(name='schema', plugins=[DjangoDebugPlugin()])

class Query(graphene.ObjectType):
    all_users = DjangoFilterConnectionField(User)
    all_profile = DjangoFilterConnectionField(Profile)
    user = relay.NodeField(User)
    profile = relay.NodeField(Profile)
    node = relay.NodeField()
    viewer = graphene.Field('self')

    def resolve_viewer(self, *args, **kwargs):
        return self

schema.query = Query

```


## My query:

