8238,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-27 17:27:04+00:00,55808787,openthread/openthread,16142208,jwhui,16142269,openthread,275769473,347257748,"@duenzhaw, exposing a secure coap functionality sounds like a great enhancement.  I'm not aware of any existing work that does this already.  The particular strategy to recommend largely depends on the use case.

On the simple end of the spectrum, the use case only requires a basic CoAP implementation and does not need to operate simultaneously with Thread Commissioning roles.  In this case, I would introduce APIs that expose the existing secure coap methods plus minimal set of methods needed for DTLS-specific configuration (certificates, etc.).  Of course, the `mbedtls-config.h` file would also need to be updated to include the necessary cipher suites are part of the build.  If you need additional CoAP functionality, we could also look to enhancing OpenThread's CoAP implementation.

On the more flexible end of the spectrum, you could utilize the mbedtls library on top of OpenThread's UDP API.  This gives you full access to the mbedtls APIs and full flexibility on memory utilization.  This would also allow you to provide a more full-featured CoAP implementation on top.  However, this would probably require more implementation effort in the near term.

Thoughts?  Are you interested in submitting a PR once we have agreed on a path forward?",{},OWNER,User,False
