8460,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-20 19:41:59+00:00,38581626,pybind/pybind11,4459524,jagerman,17565521,pybind,223134348,295875914,"It's possible, but can I ask why you'd want this?

Also worth pointing out: the template types in py::init<...> are defining arguments to forward to the constructor, not the (C++) constructor signature.  The argument types don't even have to exactly match the invoked constructor as long as the types are implicitly convertible (e.g. `py::init<int>()` will happily invoke a `MyType(long)` constructor).  The only use I can see for supporting `sometype foo(void)` is C compatibility, but that seems meaningless for a constructor definition.",{},,User,False
