8636,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-21 00:30:11+00:00,50646767,raiden-network/raiden,310139,hackaugusto,19666847,raiden-network,189372565,268399893,"So, we have these three dependencies:

- **pyethapp**.rpc_client.JSONRPCClient (used by [raiden 0.0.4](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/v0.0.4/raiden/network/rpc/client.py#L124-L129))
- **tinyrpc**.transport.http.HttpPostClientTransport (used by [pyethapp 1.5.0](https://github.com/ethereum/pyethapp/blob/v1.5.0/pyethapp/rpc_client.py#L123-L124))
- **requests**.api.request (used by [tinyrpc 0.5](https://github.com/mbr/tinyrpc/blob/0.5/tinyrpc/transports/http.py#L28))

The problem is that request's (as of 2.12.4) [creates a fresh](https://github.com/kennethreitz/requests/blob/v2.12.4/requests/api.py#L55-L56) Session for each high-level call. We need to patch tinyrpc to create a Session object instead of relying in the high-level request's api, by reusing a session we will benefit of connection reuse provided by [urllib3](https://github.com/kennethreitz/requests/blob/v2.12.4/requests/adapters.py#L123) (if supported by the ethereum node)

",{},,User,False
