8692,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-05 03:59:33+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SoS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,294240864,362975814,"The line you pointed to is for task. [this line](https://github.com/vatlab/SoS/blob/master/src/sos/actions.py#L329) is for regular execution, which says, 

```
stderr=None if env.verbosity > 0 else subprocess.DEVNULL,
                                         stdout=None if env.verbosity > 1 else subprocess.DEVNULL
```
So `v1` shows `stderr` but not `stdout`. This makes sense because `stderr` is meant for errors and should have higher priority.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
